  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6773.36 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6770 (-15.9B) and positive gamma wall at 6780 (+19.1B), dealers are likely buying any dips toward 6770 and will sell strength into 6780, creating a tight trading range. The PIN regime confirms dealers are long gamma and providing stabilizing flow, but the gex_surge event and extreme intraday GEX changes (1690% in 5 minutes) suggest heavy options flow is reshaping the hedging landscape in real-time. Key levels are the 6780 resistance where dealers turn into sellers and the 6765-6770 support zone where negative gamma creates amplified buying.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to ping-pong between 6770 and 6780 with dealers capping both sides.",
